snippet.textDisplay: Professionally or Grammatically hoyto Sunidhi flawless … but sunidhir voice e Kono pran nei, Kono sweetness nei…! Lifeless..! Perhaps Sunidhi ektu beshi concern chilo sur, tal or grammar niye..! Tai Hoyto ettoo darun Music arrangement er pore e o Sunidhir part ta ekdom lifeless lagche…, Kono passion or Emotion nai Sunidhi r voice ar gane..! Jeta kichu din age Nanditar gaan e oneeek beshi chilo..! Sunidhi is not perfect choice for this song..! She is perfect for Rabindra sangeet ..! Next time e Sunidhi ke niye emon Experiment na kora e bhalo 👎🏼👎🏼👎🏼😩🙁

snippet.textDisplay: just average....unique but not up to the mark to be in coke studio bangla...if you compare to coke studio india or pakistan it is just below average....Instruments are covering up the vocalists, just like western music,,,, but bengali music are more like rythm and touch from soul and work of vocals which is completely missing in this music,yeah sunidhis part was ok but the male singers is just beow average, lyrics are just bullshit makes no sense,  everyline is written for matching up the last words...... moreover coke studio music should be simple, strong enough to touch each bengali speaking peoples soul, which is missing here.  Man take your time you cant just release music within one or two every weeks, master pieces takes time and more research, let me give you some hints use hason raja, shah abdul karims , north bengal vawaiya songs particular place based , or the songs in local dialect where our ears cant get through,  take it as a theme and then bring your renditions or fusions iin the music but in a controlled way ,  the mass people dont care your skills or anything until you deliver what they want....at last i would be happy if you take it as a constructive criticism and love for bangla music.
